			<h1><nobr>Yunnan Thesis Collection</nobr></h1>
			<div style="text-align:left; text-indent:2em; padding-bottom:50px">
				<p>I collected lots of thesis during Wikipedia editing, then I have the idea of collecting all the history-study thesis of Yunnan. And I can also know what are the hot issues in the field of Yunnan history research. For now, I have collected more than 6,700 thesis and articles which published in journals that be listed in <span style="font-style:italic;">A Guide to the Core Journal of China</span>, and also Yunnan local journals. Due to personal preference, I payed more attention on historical geography and ethnohistory, thus these two topics may be more complete. The major journals are: (classification and ranking are just personal preference, and don't be mind the kidding names)</p>
				<p><span style="font-style:italic;">Four Heavenly Kings</span> of Yunnan Social Science: <span style="font-style:italic;">Thinking</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Social Sciences in Yunnan</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of Yunnan Minzu University</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of Yunnan Normal University</span>.</p>
				<p><span style="font-style:italic;">Three Musketeers</span> of ethnohistory: <span style="font-style:italic;">Ethno-National Studies</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of Minzu University of China</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Guizhou Ethnic Studies</span>.</p>
				<p><span style="font-style:italic;">Gang of Three</span> on historical geography: <span style="font-style:italic;">China's Borderland History and Geography Studies</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">The Chinese Historical Geography</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of Chinese Historical Geography</span>.</p>
				<p>Some quality Yunnan local journals: <span style="font-style:italic;">Studies on Ancient Books of Southwest China</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Academic Exploration</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Studies on Ethnic Groups in the Southwestern Frontier</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of Dali University</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Essays on the Ethnic Culture of Dali</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of Kunming University</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of Qujing Normal University</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of Yuxi Normal University</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of Chuxiong Normal University</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of Baoshan University</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of Zhaotong University</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of Honghe University</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of Wenshan University</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Journal of West Yunnan University</span>.</p>
				<p>The journals I still looking for, but haven't got yet: <span style="font-style:italic;">Yunnan Cultural Relics</span> (internal publication of Yunnan Provincial Museum), <span style="font-style:italic;">Essays of Nanzhao History</span> (internal publication of Dali Prefectural Nanzhao History Research Association).</p>
